crab hole
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a hole washed out of a track or road and filled with water so hiding their depth, and danger to horses (in which horses can trip).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
